I had never seen this room accommodate people who are not part of the council before. Today, it was packed with military staff -- every single top-ranking general and admiral in Rizia was in attendance.

"Let's cut the chit-chat and start with this."

"Your Majesty."

As soon as I entered the room, they stopped their chatter and saluted me. Everyone, except a man in a wheelchair, stood up.

en


"At ease, soldiers."

en


I saluted.

I arrived at the Council Chambers to discuss the war plans with the highest ranking members of the Rizian military.

en


They were standing over a massive table, arranging golden and silver tokens atop a map of Pales.

en


Lucita rushed to my side.

en


"Your Grace."

en


"Are you ready?"

en


"Of course."

en


As soon as she said that, I realized the man in the wheelchair was the famous general himself.

Narrator: Despite knowing him for years as my...
en


Despite knowing him for years as my father's Councillor for War and Security, it was difficult to recognize him as an old man.

LineNo: 13109143,

Narrator: Despite knowing him for years as my...
en


Despite knowing him for years as my father's Councillor for War and Security, as well as working with him when I joined the council myself, I had difficulty recognizing him.

LineNo: 13109245,

Narrator: Despite knowing him for years as my...
en


Despite knowing him for years as my father's Councillor for War and Security, and even serving under him in the military, I had difficulty recognizing him.

en


When we caught eyes, he saluted me.

Player_Romus_Italic: I saluted him back.
en


I saluted him back.

Salute him back.

Player_Romus: Thank you, Duchess.
en


"Thank you, Duchess."

Everyone in the room gave a military salute.

LineNo: 13109777,

Lucita Azaro: Given his unmatched expertise on m...

"Given his unmatched expertise on military strategy, I brought General Taddeus with me today."

LineNo: 13109879,

Player_Romus: Welcome back, General Taddeus Azar...
en


"Welcome back, General Taddeus Azaro."

LineNo: 13109981,

Taddeus Azaro: Glad to be of service, Your Majest...
en


"Glad to be of service, Your Majesty."

en


"Shall I start, Your Majesty?"

en


"Please."

en


I nodded in approval.

Player_Romus_Italic: I nodded in approval.

Nod.

LineNo: 13110411,

Player_Romus: Yes. What are we even waiting for?
en


"Yes. What are we even waiting for?"

LineNo: 13110513,

Lucita Azaro: Your Majesty, our forces are alrea...
en


"Your Majesty, our forces are already mobilized. Our navy and air forces are prepared and are awaiting for your orders. And our ground forces will be ready to cross the border within 48 hours."

LineNo: 13110615,

Player_Romus: And what is our intelligence on Pa...
en


"And what is our intelligence on Palesian defenses?"

LineNo: 13110717,

Player_Romus: And what is the plan for the initi...
en


"And what is the plan for the initial strike?"

LineNo: 13110819,

Player_Romus: Okay. What are our options?
en


"Okay. What are our options?"

LineNo: 13110921,

Lucita Azaro: Our intelligence suggests Pales ma...
en


"Our intelligence suggests Pales may not be completely prepared for an immediate incursion. We have the element of surprise, which we should capitalize on."

LineNo: 13111857,

Lucita Azaro: Our intelligence suggests Pales is...
en


"Our intelligence suggests Pales is expecting an immediate incursion."

LineNo: 13111959,

Lucita Azaro: However, they have been strengthen...
en


"However, they have been strengthening their northern borders with us -- building forts and bunkers along River Alca."

LineNo: 13113165,

Lucita Azaro: And, they have been strengthening...
en


"And, they have been strengthening their northern borders with us -- building forts and bunkers along River Alca."

LineNo: 13113267,

Lucita Azaro: We also received intelligence abou...
en


"We also received intelligence about the deployment of dozens hi-tech armored vehicles with unknown capabilities -- which we believe to be of Lespian origin."

LineNo: 13113369,

Lucita Azaro: We believe they've recently receiv...
en


"We believe they've recently received dozens of tanks of Lespian origin as well."

LineNo: 13113471,

Narrator: She pointed at the Antacean Sea on...
en


She pointed at the Antacean Sea on the map.

LineNo: 13113573,

Lucita Azaro: According to our intelligence, the...
en


"According to our intelligence, they have already called back their navy that was blocking the Aureus field back to the Palesian coasts."

LineNo: 13113953,

Lucita Azaro: Unfortunately, due to their recent...
en


"Unfortunately, due to their recent acquiral of a large number of Lespian destroyers, their navy is more than capable of breaking our blockade attempts."

LineNo: 13114055,

Taddeus Azaro: The general staff proposes a two-p...
en


"The general staff proposes a two-pronged attack. First, we'll need to block Palesian ports from receiving any external support and cripple their trade."

LineNo: 13114157,

Taddeus Azaro: Second, a large ground offensive a...
en


"Second, a large ground offensive aimed at securing key border defenses."

LineNo: 13114259,

Player_Romus: So, this is what we'll do...
en


"So, this is what we'll do..."

LineNo: 13114361,

Lucita Azaro: Speed is of the essence. We must o...
en


"Speed is of the essence. We must overwhelm Palesian soldiers before they can fully organize."

LineNo: 13114463,

Lucita Azaro: However, an assault from the north...
en


"However, an assault from the north would be very bloody -- especially crossing River Alca. It is their most fortified border."

LineNo: 13114859,

Lucita Azaro: However, an assault from the north...
en


"However, an assault from the north could prove to be difficult -- especially while crossing River Alca."

LineNo: 13116099,

Lucita Azaro: Unfortunately, due to their recent...
en


"Unfortunately, due to their recent acquiral of a large number of Lespian destroyers, their navy is more than capable of breaking our blockade attempts."

LineNo: 13116201,

Lucita Azaro: But according to reports, they are...
en


"But according to reports, they are already deploying thousands of soldiers along their whole border at this moment."

LineNo: 13116303,

Player_Romus: Okay. Let's talk about our deploym...
en


"Okay. Let's talk about our deployment and general strategy."

LineNo: 13116405,

WarPlanHub1

WarPlanHub1

LineNo: 13116799,

Player_Romus: Attacking from the north could pot...
en


"Attacking from the north could potentially surprise them. They wouldn't expect us to lead a grand offensive on their most fortified border."

LineNo: 13116901,

Player_Romus: What is the suggestion of the gene...
en


"What is the suggestion of the generals?"

LineNo: 13117003,

Player_Romus: How about striking from their west...
en


"How about striking from their western border?"

LineNo: 13117105,

Taddeus Azaro: Our proposal is to feign an attack...
en


"Our proposal is to feign an attack in the north to make them focus their forces there, but to spread our forces throughout the border."

LineNo: 13117207,

Taddeus Azaro: This strategy would allow us to st...
en


"This strategy would allow us to strike from the west."

LineNo: 13117309,

Taddeus Azaro: We could feign an attack in the nor...
en


We could feign an attack in the north to make them focus their forces there, but focus the bulk of our forces to the west."

LineNo: 13117411,

Taddeus Azaro: However, their western border is c...
en


"However, their western border is covered with mountains. And we believe they possess specially trained mountaineer units defending those terrains."

LineNo: 13117513,

Lucita Azaro: There is a chance we can breakthro...
en


"There is a chance we can breakthrough from their southern coast with the help of our navy."

LineNo: 13117615,

Lucita Azaro: If we can deploy our armored units...
en


"If we can deploy our armored units on that front, we can possibly push from their coast and block their supplies."

LineNo: 13117741,

Taddeus Azaro: It is indeed one of our options.
en


"It is indeed one of our options."

LineNo: 13118339,

Player_Romus: What would attacking from the nort...
en


"What would attacking from the north entail?"

LineNo: 13118441,

Taddeus Azaro: We can deploy our armored forces a...
en


"We can deploy our armored forces around Fort Ales and focus our attack on Navar.

LineNo: 13118821,

Taddeus Azaro: If we get Navar quickly, we can mo...
en


"If we get Navar quickly, we can move towards Arces and cut out the supply of their whole army."

LineNo: 13118923,

Taddeus Azaro: However, initiating an attack from...
en


"However, initiating an attack from Fort Ales would put our city in great risk. And we have to be quick enough for them not to focus their forces in the north."

LineNo: 13119041,

Player_Romus: We can also focus on a naval invas...
en


"We can also focus on a naval invasion."

LineNo: 13119143,

Player_Romus: I like the idea to feign an attack...
en


"I like the idea to feign an attack from the north to split their forces."

LineNo: 13119245,

Player_Romus: I think this is the strategy they...
en


"I think this is the strategy they would least expect."

LineNo: 13119713,

Player_Romus: I think we shouldn't risk anything...
en


"I think we shouldn't risk anything with a fake assault."

LineNo: 13119815,

Lucita Azaro: I'm afraid with our current capabi...
en


"I'm afraid with our current capabilities, it is not possible to initiate a massive naval invasion."

LineNo: 13119917,

Lucita Azaro: Our specially trained marines can...
en


"Our specially trained marines can definitely open an additional front from the south, but due to our capacity, it would be a quite limited assault."

LineNo: 13120035,

Lucita Azaro: I'm afraid with our current capabi...
en


"I'm afraid with our current capabilities, it is not possible to initiate any meaningful naval invasion."

LineNo: 13120137,

Lucita Azaro: Although our navy could potentiall...
en


"Although our navy could potentially support our land units in the south, we do not possess the capability of carrying enough troops for a successful landing."

LineNo: 13120533,

Player_Romus: What would attacking from the nort...
en


"What would attacking from the north entail?"

LineNo: 13120725,

Player_Romus: I understand.
en


"I understand."

LineNo: 13120827,

Taddeus Azaro: I'm with you on that, Your Majesty.
en


"I'm with you on that, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 13120929,

Taddeus Azaro: If they do not possess our deploym...
en


"If they do not possess our deployment plans, that might force them to keep a balanced defense throughout their border."

LineNo: 13121031,

Taddeus Azaro: I suspect that to be the case as w...
en


"I suspect that to be the case as well, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 13121133,

Taddeus Azaro: As the King, you have total contro...
en


"As the King, you have total control over our military strategy and the deployment of our troops."

LineNo: 13121235,

Taddeus Azaro: Instead, may I provide you with a...
en


"Instead, may I provide you with a briefing before we make any decisions?"

LineNo: 13121345,

Player_Romus: No. I already know everything.
en


"No. I already know everything."

LineNo: 13121447,

Player_Romus: Please, General.
en


"Please, General."

en


"What would you like to hear about first?"

WarAttackPlanStart

The room fell into a silence as everybody looked at me in anticipation of what I would say next.

en


"Your Majesty. As the King, you have total control over our military strategy and the deployment of our troops."

en


General Taddeus cut in.

Taddeus Azaro: But before you give the orders, wo...
en


"But before you give the orders, would you like to hear about the status of our military and the options the generals outlined?"

Player_Romus: Go ahead, General.
en


"Go ahead, General."

LineNo: 13122669,

Player_Romus: No. I already know everything, Gen...
en


"No. I already know everything, General. I'm ready to give you your orders, so listen carefully."

LineNo: 13122771,

Player_Romus: Do not interrupt me ever again.
en


"Do not interrupt me ever again."

LineNo: 13122873,

Narrator: He looked furious, but he refrained...
en


He looked furious, but he refrained himself from responding to me and bowed his head.

LineNo: 13122975,

Taddeus Azaro: Of course, Your Majesty.
en


"Of course, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 13123211,

Player_Romus: What's the status of our military?
en


"What's the status of our military?"

LineNo: 13123313,

Player_Romus: What are our strategic objectives?
en


"What are our strategic objectives?"

LineNo: 13123415,

Lucita Azaro: Due to the overwhelming presence o...
en


"Due to the overwhelming presence of the Palesian navy and naval defenses around Pales and the Gulf of Ales -- including the possibility of direct engagement with Lespia -- our strategy will have to rely on an attack from either the north or the southwest."

LineNo: 13123517,

Taddeus Azaro: Our first objective is to take con...
en


"Our first objective is to take control of their cities Ziqes and Arces and trap their forces in at the chokepoint at Solles."

LineNo: 13123619,

Player_Romus: Give me the details of each front...
en


"Give me the details of each front and what to expect."

LineNo: 13123817,

Player_Romus: I think I have enough information.
en


"I think I have enough information."

LineNo: 13123919,

Player_Romus: We will lead a direct assault with...
en


"We will lead a direct assault without any precursors. It is better if they spread their defenses without a clear focus."

LineNo: 13124021,

Player_Romus: Before the invasion, we will feign...
en


"Before the invasion, we will feign an attack from the north and try to get their forces to focus there."

LineNo: 13124123,

Player_Romus: Before the invasion, we will feign...
en


"Before the invasion, we will feign an attack from the south and try to get their forces to focus there."

LineNo: 13124225,

Narrator: The generals in the room gave me a...
en


The generals in the room gave me a military salute while shouting "Yes, sir."

LineNo: 13124359,

Player_Romus: I will look into it in detail, Gen...
en


"I will look into it in detail, General."

LineNo: 13124461,

Taddeus Azaro: In light of this, I'd like to send...
en


"In light of this, I'd like to send you a detailed plan for our initial deployment through the border -- focusing on a simultaneous attack towards Ziqes and the southwestern coast."

LineNo: 13124579,

Player_Romus: No offense, general, but I'll plan...
en


"No offense, general, but I'll plan the assault and the deployment of our forces personally."

LineNo: 13124681,

Player_Romus: I cannot and will not manage every...
en


"I cannot and will not manage every division and the whole war effort. I will give the complete authority of the invasion to the General Staff and you, General Azaro."

Player_Romus: I cannot and will not manage every...
Menu Text en


"I cannot and will not manage every division and the whole war effort. I will give the complete authority of the invasion to the General Staff and you, General Azaro." [OPT OUT OF WAR GAMEPLAY]

LineNo: 13124789,

Taddeus Azaro: Thank you, Your Majesty.
en


"Thank you, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 13124891,

Taddeus Azaro: Understood, Your Majesty.
en


"Understood, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 13124993,

Taddeus Azaro: Our initial operation will be aime...
en


"Our initial operation will be aimed at taking control of Arces and Ziqes."

LineNo: 13125095,

Taddeus Azaro: The city of Ziqes is located very...
en


"The city of Ziqes is located very close to our borders and it lies on the highway and railway system that runs in the middle of the country."

LineNo: 13125197,

Taddeus Azaro: Due to his proximity to our border...
en


"Due to his proximity to our borders, it is heavily defended. Unfortunately, our air forces can't be of any help before we can destroy their anti-air systems which are located in the mountains south of the city."

LineNo: 13125299,

Taddeus Azaro: Another strategic point is the tow...
en


"Another strategic point is the town of Navar, directly by our border near Fort Ales."

LineNo: 13125401,

Taddeus Azaro: Pales also has incredibly sophisti...
en


"Pales also has incredibly sophisticated anti-air defenses installed in that area -- and any attack from the north would require the capture of the area for our air forces to be able to support our operation."

LineNo: 13125503,

Narrator: He pointed at the map.
en


He pointed at the map.

LineNo: 13125605,

Taddeus Azaro: The most important goal for our in...
en


"The most important goal for our initial operation is to capture the city of Arces, situated directly in the middle of Pales."

LineNo: 13125707,

Taddeus Azaro: We have intelligence that their de...
en


"We have intelligence that their defense is organized from there and it provides supplies to every front. By cutting that city from their network, we can crush their border defenses and create a new frontline from Navar to the sea."

LineNo: 13127075,

Player_Romus: Okay. So here's what we'll do...
en


"Okay. So here's what we'll do..."

LineNo: 13127177,

Taddeus Azaro: What are your initial orders, Your...
en


"What are your initial orders, Your Majesty?"

LineNo: 13127279,

Player_Romus: Furthermore, we will keep our navy...
en


"Furthermore, we will keep our navy on standby until the assault begins. We cannot risk any reckless damage."

LineNo: 13127381,

Player_Romus: Furthermore, we will immediately f...
en


"Furthermore, we will immediately focus our Navy to blockade the Gulf of Ales. It is their most heavily guarded area but the closest to our coastline."

LineNo: 13127483,

Player_Romus: Furthermore, we will immediately f...
en


"Furthermore, we will immediately focus our Navy to blockade the Gulf of Pales. Our efforts must be focused at their capital even if that means a direct confrontation with their strongest fleet."

LineNo: 13127585,

Player_Romus: Furthermore, we will immediately f...
en


"Furthermore, we will immediately focus our Navy to blockade the Gulf of Remaz. Our efforts must be focused on disrupting their trade without a risky confrontation at the sea."

LineNo: 13127687,

Taddeus Azaro: Understood, Your Majesty.
en


"Understood, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 13133997,

Player_Romus: We will keep our navy and our mari...
en


"We will keep our navy and our marines on standby for a possible naval invasion. We cannot risk any reckless damage before the invasion begins."

LineNo: 13136505,

Lucita Azaro: As mentioned, our land armies are...
en


"As mentioned, our land armies are getting ready for action, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 13137163,

Lucita Azaro: We can currently field a large num...
en


"We can currently field a large number of infantry divisions. This is quite enough to overwhelm the Palesian forces."

LineNo: 13137265,

Lucita Azaro: We can currently field around eigh...
en


"We can currently field around eight to nine fully equipped infantry divisions. I believe this is a good number in our fight against Pales."

LineNo: 13137367,

Lucita Azaro: We can currently field around six...
en


"We can currently field around six to seven fully equipped infantry divisions. Our numbers are not too many and we should be cautious with our infantry -- who are the bulk of our forces."

LineNo: 13137469,

Lucita Azaro: We can currently field five fully...
en


"We can currently field five fully equipped infantry divisions. Palesian infantry divisions do outnumber us and we should be cautious."

LineNo: 13138405,

Lucita Azaro: Thankfully, we also have a huge nu...
en


"Thankfully, we also have a huge number of mechanized support divisions which will be incredibly useful in supporting the assaults of our infantry and armored divisions."

LineNo: 13138507,

Lucita Azaro: Thankfully, we also have quite a g...
en


"Thankfully, we also have quite a good number of mechanized support divisions which will be incredibly useful in supporting the assaults of our infantry and armored divisions."

LineNo: 13138609,

Lucita Azaro: On the other hand, we also have a...
en


"On the other hand, we also have a modest amount of mechanized support divisions which will be incredibly useful in supporting the assaults of our infantry and armored divisions."

LineNo: 13138711,

Lucita Azaro: Unfortunately, we can only field t...
en


"Unfortunately, we can only field three mechanized support divisions, which are specifically trained to support the assaults of our infantry and armored divisions."

LineNo: 13138813,

Lucita Azaro: We should not risk losing them --...
en


"We should not risk losing them -- as they can change the tide of the war."

LineNo: 13138915,

Lucita Azaro: And lastly, when it comes to our t...
en


"And lastly, when it comes to our tanks..."

LineNo: 13139851,

Lucita Azaro: Our tank divisions outnumber Pales...
en


"Our tank divisions outnumber Pales in number and they will be leading the main assault."

LineNo: 13139953,

Lucita Azaro: We currently field enough tank div...
en


"We currently field enough tank divisions to be able to lead an aggressive assault."

LineNo: 13140055,

Lucita Azaro: We currently field three tank divi...
en


"We currently field three tank divisions. Pales has far more tanks than we have."

LineNo: 13140157,

Lucita Azaro: We currently field only two tank d...
en


"We currently field only two tank divisions. Pales has far more tanks than we have."

LineNo: 13140259,

Narrator: She sighed.
en


She sighed.

LineNo: 13140361,

Narrator: She had a confident smile on her fa...
en


She had a confident smile on her face.

LineNo: 13140463,

Lucita Azaro: On the other hand, our air force i...
en


"On the other hand, our air force is capable of contesting Palesian air superiority. We can conduct bombings almost everywhere outside of the reach of their primary air defense systems -- which are not insignificant to say the least."

LineNo: 13140843,

Lucita Azaro: On the other hand, our air force i...
en


"On the other hand, our air force is barely capable of contesting Palesian air superiority. We can still try conducting bombings outside of the reach of their primary air defense systems -- which will be quite a problem."

LineNo: 13141223,

Lucita Azaro: Our admirals have reported that ou...
en


"Our admirals have reported that our specially trained marine divisions and their deployment ships will be ready to initiate a coastal invasion in no time."

LineNo: 13141603,

Lucita Azaro: And lastly, our navy is led by our...
en


"And lastly, our navy is led by our flagship RRN Valero."

LineNo: 13141705,

Lucita Azaro: And lastly, our navy has unfortuna...
en


"And lastly, our navy has unfortunately suffered a great loss with RRN Valero taken out of service."

LineNo: 13141807,

Lucita Azaro: It is also important to highlight...
en


"It is also important to highlight that despite investing greatly in our navy, they still have access to superior technology than us."

LineNo: 13141909,

Lucita Azaro: It is also important to highlight...
en


"It is also important to highlight that as much as we can contest Pales at the seas, they still have superior technology and numbers than us."

LineNo: 13142845,

Lucita Azaro: Luckily, our fleets contain a larg...
en


"Luckily, our fleets contain a large number of destroyers -- which will surely help us get the superiority on the sea."

LineNo: 13142947,

Lucita Azaro: Our fleets also contain enough num...
en


"Our fleets also contain enough number of destroyers to be able to contest the Palesian navy at critical locations."

LineNo: 13143049,

Lucita Azaro: Unfortunately, we do not have enou...
en


"Unfortunately, we do not have enough fleets to be able to counter Palesian ships in any direct confrontation."

LineNo: 13143429,

Lucita Azaro: Our submarines will also provide t...
en


"Our submarines will also provide the much needed support when necessary. We have a good number of them to be able to wreak havoc on their ships."

LineNo: 13143531,

Lucita Azaro: Our submarines will also provide t...
en


"Our submarines will also provide the much needed support when necessary. Although, we don't have too many of them, they can still wreak havoc on their ships."

LineNo: 13143827,

Player_Romus: Thank you.
en


"Thank you."

LineNo: 13144019,

Lucita Azaro: Of course.
en


"Of course."

LineNo: 13144121,

Lucita Azaro: On their northern border, they hav...
en


"On their northern border, they have several heavily fortified areas across River Alca."

LineNo: 13144223,

Narrator: She pointed to River Alca on our bo...
en


She pointed to River Alca on our border with Pales.

LineNo: 13144325,

Lucita Azaro: They also have incredibly sophisti...
en


"They also have incredibly sophisticated air defenses placed on the town of Navar -- very close to our city, Fort Ales."

LineNo: 13144427,

Lucita Azaro: These defenses will severely impac...
en


"These defenses will severely impact our capability to push for an assault from Fort Ales."

LineNo: 13144529,

Lucita Azaro: Their most defended position on th...
en


"Their most defended position on their western front is right between our city of Terador and the Palesian city of Ziqes."

LineNo: 13144631,

Narrator: She then pointed to the city of Ziq...
en


She then pointed to the city of Ziqes and the western border.

LineNo: 13144733,
